<title>USA: TABLE-Columbia Gas Q2 net income jumps.</title>
<headline>TABLE-Columbia Gas Q2 net income jumps.</headline>
<dateline>RESTON, Va. 1997-07-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>THE COLUMBIA GAS SYSTEM INC</p>
<p>				   3 Mos ended 6/30  6 Mos ended 6/30</p>
<p>  ($ millions)		    1997     1996     1997     1996</p>
<p> Total Operating Revenues     810.7   582.4  2,338.4  1,785.4</p>
<p>Operating Expenses</p>
<p>   Products Purchased	   403.6   205.9  1,303.2    757.7</p>
<p>   Operation and Maintenance  227.4   242.0    450.9    472.7</p>
<p>   Depreciation and Depletion  49.2    50.9    120.4    119.0</p>
<p>   Other Taxes		     46.2    47.6    123.0    121.8</p>
<p> Total Operating Expenses     726.4   546.4  1,997.5  1,471.2</p>
<p> Operating Income		  84.3    36.0    340.9    314.2</p>
<p>Other Income (Deductions)   Interest Income and other net 6.1    13.7     20.4     16.8</p>
<p>  Int expense, related charges(38.0)  (39.2)   (78.3)   (82.9)</p>
<p>Total Other Income (Deductions)</p>
<p>				     (31.9)  (25.5)   (57.9)   (66.1)</p>
<p> Income before Income Taxes    52.4    10.5    283.0    248.1</p>
<p> Income Taxes			17.5     2.3     85.4     88.6</p>
<p> Net Income			  34.9     8.2    197.6    159.5</p>
<p> EPS on Common Stock ($)	 0.63    0.15     3.57     3.04</p>
<p> Avg shrs (millions)	     55.4    55.0     55.3     52.5</p>
<p>NOTE: Columbia's transmission and storage segment's Q2 operating income of $66 million increased $27 million over last year.  This primarily included $19.1 million from the sale of base gas from a Columbia Transmission storage field, the sale of which was part of its overall rate settlement, as well as increased revenues from transportation and storage services plus lower operation and maintenance costs.</p>
